OMD Worldwide, an Omnicom Media Group Agency, has been named Global Media Agency of the Year2020 for the second consecutive year by Adweek, a leading advertising industry publication globally. The accolade marks the sixth time OMD has been named Adweek Global Media Agency of the year since 2010. Profiling the agency in its February 24th issue, Adweek credits OMD for sustaining the stunning 2018 comeback globally that earned it the Global Media Agency of the Year title last year. Moreover, it is also for leveraging that momentum to support the continuing investments in talent, technology and process that would make winning a repeatable process in2019, and into the new decade. In the COMvergence Media Agency New Business Barometer report released on February 25, 2020, OMD globally tops the ranking with $2,027M in net new business values. Commenting on the collective affirmation of OMD’s industry leading performance in 2019, OMD Worldwide CEO, Florian Adamski said, “OMD is starting the new decade with greater-than-ever capacity and commitment to delivering better decisions, better ideas and better outcomes – faster – for our clients all around the world.” Dwelling on the ‘constant’ rigour for Talent, Technology and Process, Managing Director, media Reach OMD Nigeria, Nitinchandra  Nandekar said: “OMD Design is our unique differentiator that fully came to life late last year; our staff has been fully trained to deliver better decisions, faster to our clients using OMD Design. ‘’OMD Design is a process which is dynamic and fully integrated to the capabilities that sit within Omni, the data platform. OMD Design guides users through every stage of the insight and planning process, democratizing access to Omni’s potential across the network.” 